cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper discusses the roles and groups in social media, which falls under the category of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories as they deal with social media analysis and user behavior.
